{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"ef9a62eb-26b3-4393-ae05-74dd02bde60c","outcome":{"verdict":"escalation","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/pipeline-selection-capability-gate/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"decision-needed","file":"src/core/command/pipeline-run.ts","title":"pipeline: design-only + custom reviewers → orphaned reviewer snapshots in job state","rationale":"When a user specifies `pipeline: design-only` in request.md Meta AND the repo has `specrunner/reviewers/*.md` files, `loadReviewerDefinitions` returns non-empty reviewers that get snapshotted into `jobState.reviewers`. `composeReviewerDescriptor(DESIGN_ONLY_DESCRIPTOR, reviewers)` then produces a descriptor with zombie steps (custom reviewers + regression-gate) appended at the tail. Because `DESIGN_ONLY_DESCRIPTOR.transitions` has `design → success → end`, the pipeline executes correctly and terminates without touching the zombie steps. However, the persisted job state contains `reviewers` that were never executed — a logical inconsistency observable by downstream tooling that inspects `jobState.reviewers`. This path was unreachable before this change (design-only was only startable via `runDesignPipeline`, a test-only/dead path). Design D6 only guarantees 'existing path not broken', not 'reviewer + design-only interaction is clean'. Functional impact: zero.","line":82,"options":[{"label":"document and defer","consequence":"The inconsistency (reviewers present in state but never executed) is acknowledged but not fixed here. A follow-up request (fast-pipeline or a cleanup request) adds reviewer snapshot filtering based on pipeline capability (e.g. checking for `code-review` in descriptor steps). Low practical risk since `pipeline: design-only` is an uncommon choice and the pipeline still terminates correctly."},{"label":"fix in this request: skip reviewer snapshotting for design-only","consequence":"Add a guard in `pipeline-run.ts` that skips `jobState.reviewers = reviewers` when the resolved pipeline descriptor does not include a reviewer-chain phase (e.g. `descriptor.steps` has no `code-review` entry). Keeps job state clean but slightly expands scope of this infra request."}]}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"tests/unit/core/command/pipeline-run-gate.test.ts","title":"PIPELINE_REGISTRY mutation in tests is file-isolated by Vitest's worker model","rationale":"T-05 inserts a fixture descriptor into PIPELINE_REGISTRY via beforeEach and removes it in afterEach. Vitest runs each test file in its own worker thread (separate module instance), so this mutation cannot contaminate registry-invariants.test.ts which asserts PIPELINE_REGISTRY has exactly 2 entries. The beforeEach/afterEach symmetry is still good practice for within-file isolation.","line":61},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/command/resume.ts","title":"Resume path intentionally skips capability gate (by design)","rationale":"ResumeCommand.prepare() does not call assertRuntimeSupportsScope. A job started with a scope-declaring pipeline on a capable runtime could be resumed on an incapable runtime. This is explicitly by design: the gate is a job-creation preflight (착수前 reject), not a resume gate. #689 checkpoint escalation serves as the backstop for the resume path."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-14T08:08:45.854Z","endedAt":"2026-06-14T08:15:29.628Z"}
